		  	<h2>Ogier Abilities</h2>
		  	<img id="sideimg" src="images/treesinging.png" alt="">
		  	<p><strong>Treesinging</strong><br>
		  	Ogier are linked with nature. Through the Songs of Growing, which have been described as "the earth itself sang", the Ogier have the power to stimulate and control the growth of trees and plants. This power has been utilised to create the massive forest groves they live in, called Steddings.</p>
		  	<img id="sideimg" src="images/waygate.jpg" alt="a cellar lit by torches on the left and right walls. Barrells and crates litter either wall. Directly ahead is a large stone door taking up the entire back wall. The door has a tree carved into it.">
		  	<p><strong>Stonework</strong><br>
		  	While not a magical ability, Ogier are naturally gifted sculptors. Their stonework appears so natural that it looks like it has been grown from the stone itself rather than broken into shape. Other races in The Wheel of Time recognise the Ogier as masters of stonework.</p>
		  	<img id="sideimg" src="images/stedding.jpg" alt="A massive tree overlooks a small stream. Climbing in a circular fashion around the trees trunk is a series of pathways and buildings can be seen built into the branches. This is an Ogier Stedding.">
		  	<p><strong>Longing</strong><br>
		  	Ogier are born and raised in magical forest groves called Steddings. These forest groves represent Safe Havens as the One Power cannot be used within them. Each Ogier is tied to the Steddings, and if they are away from a Stedding for too long it can lead to crippling depression and madness.</p>
